Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pop the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%g} onto a piece of #foil{} with half the @Butter{30%g}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the tomato parcel on the bottom shelf until softened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat. TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} before baking.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Add the @Risotto Rice{175%g} to the pan. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Boiled Water for the Risotto{600%ml}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{20%g} and @Dried Basil{1%sachet}.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid onto the pan (or cover with foil). Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

While the risotto cooks, crumble the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%g}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}, @Fresh Pesto{32%g} and the remaining butter.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed. TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the pesto chicken risotto between your #bowls{} and top with the roasted baby plum tomatoes (discard the juices from the parcel).

Scatter over the Greek style salad cheese and drizzle over the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!